AGI -&nbsp;The Prosecutor of Milan has seized of urgency 46,8 million euros >a Dhl express Italy within an investigation for a alleged tax fraud Iva from 2019 to 2023 with non-existent invoices on labour supply contracts.
The investigations of the economic-financial police core of the Gdf in Milan and the Nil dei Carabinieri>, coordinated by the pm Paolo Storari and Valentina Mondovì, have discovered the new presumed complex tax fraud deriving from the use, by the final company, Dhl express Italy of the unlawful mechanism of invoices for transactions legally nonexistent > in the face of the stipulation of thick contracts of contract for the administration of labor >, in violation of the norm of sector, which has led to the issue and the consequent use of false documents. It is not the first company of the logistics giant and shipment controlled by the German Posts: already over 20 million had been seized in June 2021 at Dhl Supply Chain Italy.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
The Carabinieri Labour Protection Command, on behalf of the Milan Prosecutor, controlled 918 workers employed > by Dhl Express Italy, of which 676 respondents on working conditions >, pay and procedures for carrying out the activity. The inspections took place in 30 provinces of Italy. 538 means have been tested, 51 contractors of the delivery service of which 15 are irregular (violations on safety, omitted or irregular training and information, omitted health surveillance). In the province of Milan seven workers were identified under conditions of exploitation, > of which 3 were employed also in black. Altogether, 11 persons have been reported to the prosecutor or legal representatives of the companies inspected.
